org.sliderule.stats

Class Histogram

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sliderule.stats.Histogram

  • public final class Histogram
extends java.lang.Object
    This class provides methods to generate a Histogram based on a given number, or a guessed number of suitable partitions.
    See Also:
    • Wikipedia: Histogram
    • DeGroot, Morris H., and Schervish, Mark J. Probability and Statistics, 3rd Ed. Toronto: Addison-Wesley, 2002. pp. 776-778. Print.
    • Wikipedia: Scott's normal reference rule

      • binWidth

        public static double binWidth(int n,
              double o)
        Calculate the bin width that is optimal for random samples of normally distributed data. The returned bin width is optimal in the MMSE sense.
        Parameters:
        n - number of samples
        o - sample standard deviation
        Returns:
        bin width

      • partition

        public static int partition(int n,
            double o,
            double lowest,
            double highest)
        Determine an optimum number of partitions such that the bin width is optimal for a set of data.
        Parameters:
        n - number of samples in the data set
        o - sample standard deviation of the data set
        lowest - the lowest datum measured in the data set
        highest - the highest datum measured in the data set
        Returns:
        the number of partitions
